<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js"></script>

jQuery is a library for js and was made to make the language more effective 

document.querySelector("h1") === jQuery("h1") === $("h1"); 

In order to implement jQuery you have to use fetch the cdn: 
It is important that it is above the other js links 

The dollar sign is both querySelector and querySelectorAll

jQuery and DOM 
    $("h1").addClass("className"); 
    $("h1").removeClass("className");
    $("h1").hasClass("className"); - Returns a boolean value 
    
    If i console log the .attr("class") of a DOM-element it gets the values inside the class of h1  
    $("a").attr("src") - Adds a html attribute
    $("a").attr("src", "https://www.youtube.com/") - Adds a html attribute + value inside it


$("h1").text("Some text") - Changes/adds everything inside the parenthesis, ignores html  
$("h1").html("<b>Some text"</b>) - Same as .text but better because I can add html code  


Click 
    - The click listener does not need a loop to run through an array 

Adding DOM-elements 
    $("h1").before("button") - adds the button before the h1 
    $("h1").after("button") - adds the button after the h1
    $("h1").prepend("button") - adds the button before and inside the h1  
    $("h1").append("button") - adds the button after and inside the h1  
